{{Infobox journal | title = Applied and Environmental Microbiology | cover = | caption = | former_name = Applied Microbiology | abbreviation = Appl. Environ. Microbiol. | discipline = Biology | editor = Harold L. Drake | publisher = [[American Society for Microbiology]] | country = [[United States]] | history = 1953 to present | frequency = biweekly | openaccess = | license = | impact = 3.633 | impact-year = 2017 | ISSNlabel = | ISSN = 0099-2240 | eISSN = 1098-5336 | CODEN = | JSTOR = | LCCN = | OCLC = | website = http://aem.asm.org/ | link1 = | link1-name = | link2 = <!-- up to |link5= --> | link2-name = <!-- up to |link5-name= --> | boxwidth = }}
'''''Applied and Environmental Microbiology''''' is a biweekly [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[scientific journal]] published by the [[American Society for Microbiology]]. It was established in 1953 as '''''Applied Microbiology''''' and obtained its current name in 1975. Articles older than six months are available free of cost from the website, however, the newly published articles within six months are available to subscribers only. According to the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', the journal has a 2017 [[impact factor]] of 3.633.<ref name=WoS>{{cite book |year=2017 |chapter=Applied and Environmental Microbiology |title=2017 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |edition=Science |accessdate=|series=[[Web of Science]] |postscript=.}}</ref> The journal has been ranked as one of the top 100 journals over the past 100 years in the fields of biology and medicine.<ref>[[Special Libraries Association]], [http://dbiosla.org/publications/resources/dbio100.htmlTop 100 Journals in last 100 years]{{dead link|date=October 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> The current [[editor-in-chief]] is Harold L. Drake ([[University of Bayreuth]]).
The journal's scope includes "(a) applied microbiology, including [[biotechnology]], [[protein engineering]], [[bioremediation]], and [[food microbiology]], (b) [[microbial ecology]], including environmental, organismic, and [[genomic microbiology]], and (c) interdisciplinary microbiology, including invertebrate microbiology, [[plant microbiology]], aquatic microbiology, and [[geomicrobiology]]".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://aem.asm.org/ |title=Applied and Environmental Microbiology |publisher=American Society for Microbiology |work= |accessdate=2012-04-24}}</ref>
